  "text": "A list of evolutionary breakpoint regions was obtained from [CITATION_1] . We used regions defined at 100 kb resolution only; also all duplicated regions (reused breakpoints) were removed. Remaining regions were converted to GalGal5 genome coordinates using NCBI Remap tool, which resulted in 2036 regions. A rare long evolutionary breakpoint regions spanning more than one bin (more than 40 kb) were split into consecutive regions, with the length of each equal to 40 kb.",
